Photo, Beyond the Call of Duty: Deputy Roy Burns' daughter inspects medal he 
was awarded for meritorious conduct. He and Deputy Drew Birtness were honored 
Friday for saving the life of another officer who was held at gunpoint on Aug. 
9, 1989. Deputy Steven Smith was awarded the Medal of Valor -- the department's 
highest honor -- for his courageous attempt to save the driver of a burning car 
Nov. 24, 1989. Left, Sheriff's Academy graduates congratulate each other after 
becoming deputies. MINDY SCHAUER / Los Angeles Times 
